text: Celida Cordova (born 1 August 1980) is a Mexican volleyball player. She played at the 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2007 Women's NORCECA Volleyball Championship. She played for Monterrey and Durango. == References == Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican volleyball players
